%N A393987 Expansion of g.f.: Product_{k>=1} (1 + x^(k*(k+3)/2)).
%C A393987 a(n) is the number of partitions of n into distinct parts of the form k*(k+3)/2.
%H A393987 Vaclav Kotesovec, <a href="/A393987/b393987.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..10000</a>
%F A393987 a(n) ~ exp(3*Pi^(1/3) * ((sqrt(2)-1)*Zeta(3/2))^(2/3) * n^(1/3) / 2^(4/3)) * ((sqrt(2)-1)*Zeta(3/2))^(1/3) / (2^(8/3) * sqrt(3) * Pi^(1/3) * n^(5/6)).
%t A393987 nmax = 200; CoefficientList[Series[Product[1 + x^(k*(k+3)/2), {k, 1, Floor[Sqrt[9+8*nmax]/2]}], {x, 0, nmax}], x]
%Y A393987 Cf. A024940, A319799, A393989.
